Question 8:

Compare the forecast of the models from Questions 5 and 7 for July 1 8:00, 9:00, 17:00 and 18:00, which model is better (Questions 4 or 6)?

weekly_model_error = sum((df_test[c(8,9,17,18)] - July1_predicted_week$mean[c(8,9,17,18)])^2)
hourly_model_error = sum((df_test[c(8,9,17,18)] - July1_predicted_hour$mean[c(8,9,17,18)])^2)

cat("Weekly Model Error: ", weekly_model_error, "\n")
## Weekly Model Error:  4604.173
cat("Hourly Model Error: ", hourly_model_error, "\n")
## Hourly Model Error:  265420.8

From above result, we can see that the weekly model in Q4 has a smaller sum of errors than the hourly model in Q6. Therefore, the model in Question 4 is better.
